submapp.map2d.Map2d.rmse_with_respect_to_depth¶

Map2d.rmse_with_respect_to_depth(depth: numpy.ndarray)¶

Computes the RMSE of the map for each variables at each depth levels. This method uses the values and true_values attributes of the map. It means that it will compute the RMSE according to the data passed in the last call of the map method.

Parameters

depth (np.ndarray) – Vector of depth levels

Returns

Dataframe of the RMSE for each variable

Return type

pd.DataFrame
